  "prompt": "What is the typical career progression at Deloitte?",
  "response": "At Deloitte, a typical career progression often follows this path:\n\n1. Entry Level Positions\n- Analyst/Staff Consultant (0-2 years)\n- Start in a specific practice area like Audit, Consulting, Tax, or Advisory\n\n2. Mid-Level Positions\n- Senior Analyst/Senior Consultant (2-4 years)\n- Increased responsibilities and client management\n- More technical expertise in their specific domain\n\n3. Advanced Positions\n- Manager (4-6 years)\n- Lead project teams\n- Responsible for client relationships and project delivery\n- More strategic decision-making\n\n4. Senior Management\n- Senior Manager/Director (6-8 years)\n- Greater leadership responsibilities\n- Business development and client acquisition\n- Practice area specialization\n\n5. Partnership Track\n- Principal/Partner (8-10+ years)\n- Highest leadership level\n- Significant revenue generation\n- Strategic firm leadership\n- Equity ownership potential\n\nKey advancement factors include:\n- Performance\n- Client feedback\n- Technical skills\n- Leadership abilities\n- Business development\n- Continuous learning and professional development\n\nProgression can vary by practice area and individual performance, but this represents a general career trajectory at Deloitte.",
